AXA Financial, Inc. is a member of the global AXA Group and a provider of financial protection and wealth management services. AXA Group's operations are diverse geographically with its main operations in Western Europe, North America, and the Asia/Pacific region.

In… MoreAXA Financial, Inc. is a member of the global AXA Group and a provider of financial protection and wealth management services. AXA Group's operations are diverse geographically with its main operations in Western Europe, North America, and the Asia/Pacific region.

In the United States, AXA Group operates as AXA Financial, Inc. and has a number of subsidiaries, including AXA Advisors, LLC; AXA Equitable Life Insurance; AXA Network; Mutual of New York (MONY); US Financial Life; and AllianceBernstein (maintained in a separate profile).
• AXA Financial Inc. maintains a $100,000-$250,000 hardware support maintenance contract with IBM.
• AXA Financial Inc. maintains a $100,000-$250,000 legacy application support contract with CSC.
• AXA Financial Inc. maintains a $250,000-$1M help desk management contract with Dell.

2013 and Earlier:
AXA Financial,… More• AXA Financial Inc. maintains a $100,000-$250,000 hardware support maintenance contract with IBM.
• AXA Financial Inc. maintains a $100,000-$250,000 legacy application support contract with CSC.
• AXA Financial Inc. maintains a $250,000-$1M help desk management contract with Dell.

2013 and Earlier:
AXA Financial, Inc. is a member of the global AXA Group and a provider of financial protection and wealth management services. AXA Group's operations are diverse geographically with its main operations in Western Europe, North America, and the Asia/Pacific region.

In the United States, AXA Group operates as AXA Financial, Inc. and has a number of subsidiaries, including AXA Advisors, LLC; AXA Equitable Life Insurance; AXA Network; Mutual of New York (MONY); US Financial Life; and AllianceBernstein (maintained in a separate profile).

IT STRUCTURE AXA Financial is the American segment of AXA Group, based in Paris. The IT department for AXA Group is a separate subsidiary at the company, AXA Technology Services, known as AXA Tech. Less than 10 percent of AXA Tech's 3,300-person worldwide staff works in the United States, but that ratio belies the number of key company-wide IT decision-makers based here.  Most US AXA Tech employees work at AXA Tech's primary office in Jersey City, NJ, but others operate from AXA Financial's headquarters in New York, NY, and AXA Equitable's office in Syracuse, NY. AXA Equitable is the main business line of AXA Financial. The employees at AXA Financial and AXA Equitable are not officially part of AXA Tech, and that is why the number of IT employees in the US is much higher than the 300-range. The main operator in New York can direct callers to employees in Jersey City; the number published on the AXA Tech website as of spring 2012 for the Jersey City office is incorrect. AXA Tech is a centralized organization that takes overall direction from executives in Paris. The subsidiary was created to do much of the work in house, but dozens of solutions from outside vendors are used as well.  The two leading US officials at AXA Tech are the Chief Operations Officer for IT and the Chief Information Officer. The other three highest-ranking executives are the Chief Technology Officer, Chief Information Security Officer, and Chief Privacy Officer (CPO). All are in Jersey City save the CPO, a position with significant IT responsibilities.  In the past two years, high-level executives from the US IT team have transitioned to positions leading AXA Tech operations in Hong Kong, Japan, and Mexico. The latter executive remains based in the US despite a mission to build out AXA Tech's newest region.  AXA Rosenberg is a small subsidiary based in Orinda, CA. IT INFORMATION SNIPPITS •Like many global conglomerates, AXA Tech strives to streamline and consolidate operations worldwide, often with an eye toward green IT. A global Transformation Office, with some leadership in the US, oversees efforts to unify IT across the whole business. Windows 7 was fully rolled out in the US in April 2012. In 2011-12, the company is deploying IBM MDM and InfoSphere. The company operates in an SAP ERP environment and relies on IBM and VMware for many of its infrastructure needs. •The company uses VSphere as its storage security solution, and checkpoint for its fraud detection. •AXA Financial Inc. has the following security safeguards in place: regular policy reviews, inventory of personal employee and customer data, inventory of locations where data is stored, documented incident response process, inventory of third parties, encryption of mobile devices, malware and virus protection software on all devices, has a documented incident response process, has a regular compliance review process, provides application access and manage identities for >10,000 customers/vendors, and has a continuous compliance model in place, and operates under HIPAA compliance regimes.   •The company uses home-grown solution to monitor threats across its networks, security devices, and data.  •It already has some security solution outsourcing in place.    •The company, AXA Financial Inc. is currently evaluating cloud solutions for a possible implementation.  The company currently runs business applications in a cloud environment, and senior sources report control / billing, are the company's biggest cloud related security concerns. •AXA Financial Inc. has a company-wide BYOD program in place.    •The IT budget is typically finalized in Q1.





